00:33:14.540 --> 00:33:18.060
He started collecting tags ever since he noticed a weird pattern.

00:33:18.700 --> 00:33:22.860
Every pair of underpants he ever got was approved by one inspector.

00:33:23.820 --> 00:33:25.740
34, you did it again!

00:33:27.500 --> 00:33:29.980
At first, he thought it was a coincidence.

00:33:30.620 --> 00:33:38.860
But as he went day after day without binding, without chafing, in complete snugness,

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:44.300
he finally understood, Inspector 34 was really your guardian angel.

00:33:48.510 --> 00:33:54.190
Strange as it sounded, Pete knew Inspector 34 was out there watching over him.

00:33:55.070 --> 00:33:59.150
And as we were all about to learn, he was absolutely right.

00:34:21.980 --> 00:35:10.900
They say that at first, no one believed in the theories of Christopher Columbus and Albert

00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:15.060
Einstein. So I guess Pete was in pretty good company.

00:35:16.340 --> 00:35:18.900
I don't care how snug they fit. You're nuts.

00:35:19.780 --> 00:35:21.300
Guardian angel?

00:35:22.180 --> 00:35:22.820
Get help.

00:35:25.790 --> 00:35:28.430
It wasn't hard to think my brother was crazy.

00:35:30.030 --> 00:35:35.790
Every day, he sent fan letters to Krebo the Loom to show Inspector 34 his appreciation.

00:35:36.670 --> 00:35:42.270
And every night, he fired up his landing pad, hoping Inspector 34 would show.

00:35:43.550 --> 00:35:49.630
To tell you the truth, I kind of figured Inspector 34 was just a man in a factory myself

00:35:50.430 --> 00:35:56.270
until the next day. It began when me and Ellen were practicing for our school band,

00:35:56.270 --> 00:36:02.430
the Fighting Squids. This year, instead of spelling squid, the band was forming a squid shape.

00:36:03.630 --> 00:36:08.590
And we were auditioning together for the coveted part of the left tentacle.

00:36:08.590 --> 00:36:19.710
What's that, Pete? After all those letters to the factory,

00:36:20.270 --> 00:36:36.110
all I got were these lousy underpants.

00:36:36.110 --> 00:36:40.830
Pete, urgent. Meet me Thursday night at 9 o'clock PM behind the Pine Disinfectant Plant.

00:36:41.550 --> 00:36:42.750
Inspector 34?

00:36:44.190 --> 00:36:45.710
He needs me.

00:36:45.710 --> 00:37:03.820
Don't shake it. Twist the lid one quarter turn to the right.

00:37:07.310 --> 00:37:12.110
The Krebstarr 9300 series has a defect in the positive battery terminal.

00:37:14.240 --> 00:37:19.680
Pete Wrigley, I've watched you grow from a toddler three to a 14 regular.

00:37:20.480 --> 00:37:22.400
Inspector 34!

00:37:23.120 --> 00:37:27.280
I'm sorry to drag you out like this.

00:37:30.140 --> 00:37:31.020
Name it.

00:37:31.020 --> 00:37:34.220
What am I thinking? I can't ask this of you.

00:37:34.220 --> 00:37:40.780
Wait! I know 24 knots, and I'm well trained in high explosives. Let me help.

00:37:40.780 --> 00:37:45.020
It's not like that. The work I do is very important.

00:37:45.980 --> 00:37:49.580
If I miss one flaw well, you know it's at stake.

00:37:50.540 --> 00:37:57.020
And yet, sometimes I wonder, is there more to life than underpants?

00:37:57.020 --> 00:38:00.860
Have I struggled so hard for perfection that life is passing me by?

00:38:02.300 --> 00:38:07.020
You seem to know how to have fun, how to cut loose, as they say.

00:38:08.460 --> 00:38:12.300
I was wondering, can you teach me?

00:38:18.420 --> 00:38:22.660
Dad, this is a friend of mine. Inspector 34.

00:38:23.620 --> 00:38:26.100
Inspector 34, yeah, and I am...

00:38:26.100 --> 00:38:28.580
Don Wrigley, 37 stout down from 38.

00:38:29.460 --> 00:38:30.100
That's right.

00:38:30.740 --> 00:38:33.860
Joyce, the way you stay size six is an inspiration.

00:38:34.660 --> 00:38:38.180
Pete, Ellen, you've grown so fast, it's hard to keep up.

00:38:39.060 --> 00:38:39.860
