I'm designing the perfect bike.

01:48:40.740 --> 01:48:44.020
It's tall and it looks like a Harley Davidson.

01:48:44.020 --> 01:48:44.980
Awesome.

01:48:44.980 --> 01:48:46.740
I could really get into this.

01:48:46.740 --> 01:49:07.240
It's about taking places you've never been before.

01:49:08.120 --> 01:49:08.920
Watch out.

01:49:08.920 --> 01:49:09.960
It's coming back.

01:49:09.960 --> 01:49:12.200
We now return to Are You Afraid of the Dark?

01:49:13.480 --> 01:49:16.280
Ew.

01:49:16.280 --> 01:49:17.240
Let's get out of here.

01:49:17.320 --> 01:49:20.620
It's Mrs. Hurley.

01:49:20.620 --> 01:49:22.780
Mr.

01:49:22.780 --> 01:49:24.780
No talking in the library.

01:49:25.740 --> 01:49:26.940
That's not Mrs. Hurley.

01:49:27.660 --> 01:49:29.980
There's room for two more.

01:49:29.980 --> 01:49:34.570
Who are you?

01:49:35.130 --> 01:49:55.690
Who was that?

01:49:55.690 --> 01:49:56.570
What happened to your voice?

01:49:57.530 --> 01:49:57.930
Come on.

01:50:05.050 --> 01:50:05.690
Try the others.

01:50:06.250 --> 01:50:13.850
Looking forward.

01:50:16.390 --> 01:50:16.870
They're gone.

01:50:18.150 --> 01:50:19.350
It's a fire alarm.

01:50:19.350 --> 01:50:20.550
It's gone too.

01:50:20.550 --> 01:50:21.990
Everything modern is gone.

01:50:21.990 --> 01:50:23.110
Jace, what is going on?

01:53:54.360 --> 01:53:55.240
It's doing in here.

01:53:59.020 --> 01:53:59.820
How did you get in?

01:54:00.380 --> 01:54:29.660
Well, I'm there.

01:54:29.740 --> 01:55:06.330
I ought to call this in.

01:55:06.970 --> 01:55:16.970
You kids stay put.

01:55:16.970 --> 01:55:20.410
Whoever they were, I think they're free now.

01:55:20.410 --> 01:55:45.860
But they're never going to believe us, are they?

01:55:46.740 --> 01:55:48.180
I'm not sure I'll believe us.

01:55:48.900 --> 01:55:51.780
You know, maybe we're not such a bad team after all.

01:55:51.780 --> 01:55:53.060
Is this anybody's?

01:55:53.060 --> 01:55:54.260
My notebook.

01:55:54.260 --> 01:55:56.180
Your kids can go now if they need you a call.

01:55:56.180 --> 01:56:06.580
You still have to write the paper.

01:56:07.540 --> 01:56:08.260
We?

01:56:08.260 --> 01:56:09.060
Come on.

01:56:09.060 --> 01:56:33.270
Let's live dangerously.

01:56:33.270 --> 01:56:36.390
Yeah, I never knew silence could be so creepy.

01:56:36.390 --> 01:56:40.550
I declare this meeting of the Midnight Society closed.

01:56:40.550 --> 01:56:43.990
Speaking of libraries, I have some books I have to return.

01:56:43.990 --> 01:56:45.430
Does anyone want to keep me company?

01:56:45.430 --> 01:56:46.950
But it's way past closing.

01:56:46.950 --> 01:56:48.630
I was going to chop them in the night slot.

01:56:48.630 --> 01:56:49.270
Who's with me?

01:56:49.910 --> 01:56:50.710
I gotta go.

01:56:51.270 --> 01:56:51.750
Yeah.

01:56:53.270 --> 01:56:55.830
Go and look at the time.

01:56:55.830 --> 01:56:58.790
See you guys next time.

01:56:58.790 --> 01:57:00.630
Hasta la vista.

01:57:00.630 --> 01:57:01.670
Tucker.

01:57:01.670 --> 01:57:01.990
Bye.

01:57:02.710 --> 01:57:03.270
Come on.

01:57:03.270 --> 01:57:04.150
Just leave me at the clock.

01:57:04.150 --> 01:58:37.780
Back in just 166 hours uncounted.

01:58:37.780 --> 01:58:41.540
I'll wrap this here.

